				\begin{document}$${J}_{MAPD}={\int }_{\lambda =300\,nm\,}^{\lambda =1200nm}\frac{e\lambda }{hc}I(\lambda )A(\lambda )d\lambda $$\end{document}Here, I(λ) is the intensity of the AM1.5G spectrum. We assume that each absorbed photon creates a single electron-hole pair. The short-circuit current (JSC) of an ideal cell, without any surface and bulk recombination losses, coincides with JMAPD.

